<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert">
    <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>&nbsp;This step is normally used in a real proctoring tool to allow the proctor to validate the candidate attempt. Since this is a devkit, <strong>no actual candidate validation</strong> will be done here.<br/>
</div>
<div class="card bg-light">
    <div class="card-header">
        <i class="fas fa-sign-in-alt"></i>&nbsp;Continue to platform
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
            <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i>&nbsp;To <strong>continue</strong> the proctoring launch flow, click on the button below to <strong>return to the platform</strong> with a <strong><code>LtiStartAssessment</code></strong> message.
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-footer text-muted">
        <form action="{{ path('tool_message_proctoring_response') }}" method="post">
            <input type="hidden" name="registration" value="{{ token.registration.identifier }}"/>
            <input type="hidden" name="resource-link-id" value="{{ token.payload.resourceLink.identifier }}"/>
            <input type="hidden" name="start-assessment-url" value="{{ token.payload.proctoringStartAssessmentUrl }}"/>
            <input type="hidden" name="session-data" value="{{ token.payload.proctoringSessionData }}"/>
            <input type="hidden" name="attempt-number" value="{{ token.payload.proctoringAttemptNumber }}"/>
            <input type="hidden" name="verified-user-name" value="{{ token.payload.token.claims.get('name') }}"/>
            <div class="btn-group float-right" role="group" aria-label="Basic example">
                <button type="submit" class="btn-primary btn">
                    <i class="fas fa-sign-in-alt"></i>&nbsp;Launch LtiStartAssessment
                </button>
            </div>
        </form>
    </div>
</div>
